 Let's simplify the given expression in the question step by step. 

Given expression: $\frac{(10r^3)(4r^6)}{8r^4}$.

\begin{align*}
\text{Step 1: First multiply the coefficients}\\
&= \frac{40r^9}{8r^4}
\end{align*}

\begin{align*}
\text{Step 2: Next divide now}\\
&= \frac{500r^5}{1} \hspace{0.5cm} ( \text{since } \frac{r^9}{r^4} = r^{9-4} = r^5 \text{ and } \frac{40}{8} = 5 )
